<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-139-035 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 076 235</DOCID><JOURNAL>DEC User  June 1991 p37(1).andM;ne</JOURNAL><TITLE>Reflections on communication. (Software Review ) (Mirror III datacommunications software)(includes related article on value)(evaluation)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Eddison, John.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Mirror III, from Softklone in the UK, is powerful communicationssoftware and is a good value.andP;  The program is especially usefulfor online information sources such as Prestel or for traditionalmainframe access.andP;  Documentation is well presented and cleverlywritten.andP;  Mirror III is compatible with MS-DOS 2.0 and higher.andO;Memory requirements are a minimal 192Kbytes RAM; however, add/incapability requires additional memory.andP;  For operation on DECmachines, Mirror III emulates VT52, VT100 and VT220 terminals.andO;Additional emulation is possible for IBM terminals, Prestel andMinitel.andP;  File transfer protocols include Kermit, Xmodem, Ymodem,Crosstalk, Hayes and Compuserve B. Prism is bundled with MirrorIII for automation of communications and for numericalcalculations and sorting.andP;  The product could be improved with morehelp for novice users.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   SoftKlone Distributing Corp. (Products).andO;Product:   Mirror III (Communications software) (evaluation).andO;Topic:     EvaluationCommunications SoftwareNetwork Software.andO;Feature:   illustrationtable.andO;Caption:   Enhancements. (table)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>